    "client_msg_id": "6cc33697-5982-40e8-a3cc-6f9aec3c5a52",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Often when I'm discussing Dynamicland, I get the question: \"why not just use a giant iPad\"\n\nThe only response I can come up with:\n-  tactile manipulation is often necessary for learning\n- familiar objects, like paper and glue, provide well-defined affordances which cause minimal surprise, as opposed to anything in an iPad which will have surprising limitations",
